WEBVTT

00:11.917 --> 00:13.542
[Ray]
Previously on  Ray Donovan...

00:13.542 --> 00:14.709
[girl]
You like Donellen.

00:14.709 --> 00:16.834
Yeah, it's a girls' school.

00:16.834 --> 00:18.792
If they want to keep us from
boys, they shouldn't send us

00:18.792 --> 00:20.208
- boys as teachers.
- [phone beeps]

00:22.625 --> 00:23.959
This is a sound contract.

00:23.959 --> 00:26.959
You've got 3%
of the deal, Mr. Football.

00:26.959 --> 00:28.291
Hut, hut, hike.

00:28.291 --> 00:30.000
I'm Helen Miller--
Fish and Game.

00:30.000 --> 00:31.667
[Paige]
She is gonna fix

00:31.667 --> 00:32.917
the bird situation
at the field.

00:32.917 --> 00:34.500
Well, even if
she takes the money,

00:34.500 --> 00:36.917
Napier's demanding $90 million
for those apartments.

00:36.917 --> 00:38.500
Sort out Napier next.

00:38.500 --> 00:40.291
Kate McPherson--
she's a reporter.

00:40.291 --> 00:41.792
She's gonna publish an article
that says

00:41.792 --> 00:42.834
I paid him to kill Mickey.

00:42.834 --> 00:45.875
She has to be stopped.

00:45.875 --> 00:47.000
[Lena]
Kate McPherson is dead.

00:47.000 --> 00:49.333
Ray, we have to
make things right.

00:49.333 --> 00:50.291
Go fuck yourself.

00:50.291 --> 00:52.750
I love you, Teresa.

00:52.750 --> 00:54.083
Will you marry me?

00:54.083 --> 00:55.750
Are you fucking serious?

00:55.750 --> 00:57.333
Fucking Armenians
came over to collect, Pop.

00:57.333 --> 00:59.792
- How much are they after?
- 30,000.

00:59.792 --> 01:02.125
- You got the money?
- I'm a resourceful person.

01:02.125 --> 01:03.875
Hey, what the fuck
is this--funny money?

01:05.667 --> 01:08.667
Sometimes you got to push back
to get some respect.

01:08.667 --> 01:10.166
[Ray]
The envelope

01:10.166 --> 01:11.709
you gave your father
at the studio--

01:11.709 --> 01:13.000
- What was in it?
- A love letter...

01:13.000 --> 01:14.375
from my father
to my husband.

01:14.375 --> 01:15.458
That was the deal--

01:15.458 --> 01:17.333
the letter for the team.

01:17.333 --> 01:19.375
Mr. Donovan,
I'm Thomas Romero.

01:19.375 --> 01:21.500
After he left the Paraclete,
Father O'Connor and I

01:21.500 --> 01:23.000
spoke twice a day.

01:23.000 --> 01:24.333
Then his body was found,
and I knew

01:24.333 --> 01:25.834
his past had caught up
with him.

01:25.834 --> 01:28.542
Repent--repent now
or face excommunication.

01:30.500 --> 01:32.000
I'll kill you and every one
of these fucking freaks

01:32.000 --> 01:33.333
you got hiding in here!

01:33.333 --> 01:34.917
In the name of God,
the all-powerful Father,

01:34.917 --> 01:36.291
I deprive you
of the Communion

01:36.291 --> 01:37.834
of the Body and Blood
of Our Lord.

01:37.834 --> 01:40.000
You think
I fucking care, huh?

01:40.000 --> 01:41.375
I don't know many men
like you.

01:41.375 --> 01:43.667
The men I know want money
and power.

01:43.667 --> 01:45.333
You don't give a fuck
about those things.

01:45.333 --> 01:46.875
How do you know?

01:46.875 --> 01:47.917
'Cause you're addicted
to the fight.

01:47.917 --> 01:49.125
I got to go, Paige.

01:49.125 --> 01:50.375
No, you don't.

01:59.583 --> 02:03.417
[pickax pounding,
Ray grunting]

02:05.125 --> 02:08.208
♪ mysterious music ♪

02:08.208 --> 02:13.291
♪♪♪

02:26.208 --> 02:27.500
[groans]

02:27.500 --> 02:29.250
Bad dream?

02:29.250 --> 02:31.750
Yeah.

02:31.750 --> 02:32.667
I don't sleep much either.

02:37.667 --> 02:41.417
Defenses down--
fucking thoughts come in.

02:41.417 --> 02:42.250
Dreams.

02:47.583 --> 02:49.125
I should go.

02:49.125 --> 02:54.208
♪♪♪

03:26.959 --> 03:28.041
Hey, Terry.

03:31.291 --> 03:33.000
What time is it?

03:33.000 --> 03:34.667
Ray said you don't want
to move in with us?

03:34.667 --> 03:38.000
[sighs]

03:38.000 --> 03:39.417
Your kids don't want
to wake up

03:39.417 --> 03:42.041
and see all this shit.

03:42.041 --> 03:44.834
Give me
a fucking break, Terry.

03:44.834 --> 03:45.959
They've seen worse.

03:45.959 --> 03:49.667
Abby, I'm trying
to sleep here.

03:49.667 --> 03:52.792
When was the last time
you had a fucking haircut, hmm?

03:52.792 --> 03:54.625
You look
like a fucking caveman.

03:54.625 --> 03:56.500
Come on, get up.
Up.

04:00.000 --> 04:03.083
[tires screech]

04:11.208 --> 04:12.834
What is this?

04:12.834 --> 04:15.750
He's breaking ties,
Varick.

04:15.750 --> 04:17.000
[scoffs]

04:17.000 --> 04:18.959
You'll find
the terms fair.

04:18.959 --> 04:20.917
[dog barking in the distance]

04:20.917 --> 04:23.709
♪ brooding music ♪

04:23.709 --> 04:27.041
♪♪♪

04:27.041 --> 04:29.583
Uh, this is unacceptable.

04:29.583 --> 04:32.458
You're a capable man.
You'll land on your feet.

04:32.458 --> 04:37.291
♪♪♪

04:48.750 --> 04:50.709
What are you--

04:52.500 --> 04:54.750
Are you kidding me?

04:54.750 --> 04:57.000
Finney.

04:57.000 --> 05:00.417
Andrew, come on,
we need to discuss this.

05:02.083 --> 05:05.083
Finn!

05:05.083 --> 05:07.333
Finn!

05:16.041 --> 05:19.250
I made coffee.

05:19.250 --> 05:21.417
Ray, we need
to talk business.

05:21.417 --> 05:23.500
The owner's committee
needs proof that we've secured

05:23.500 --> 05:25.000
the site by week's end,

05:25.000 --> 05:26.458
or else they won't approve
the move.

05:26.458 --> 05:28.041
Can you pay Napier's price?

05:28.041 --> 05:29.250
My father says $90 million

05:29.250 --> 05:31.333
is not a rational number
for that parcel.

05:31.333 --> 05:32.792
You're gonna
have to be pretty persuasive

05:32.792 --> 05:34.250
to make him come down
by end of week.

05:34.250 --> 05:36.667
Well, then be persuasive.

05:36.667 --> 05:38.458
If he doesn't sell us
the land,

05:38.458 --> 05:40.625
then our little dream
dies on the vine.

05:53.125 --> 05:56.125
There's sugar on the counter
in the Wedgewood.

05:56.125 --> 05:59.083
Thanks.

05:59.083 --> 06:02.125
[music playing on stereo]

06:02.125 --> 06:07.208
♪♪♪

06:12.875 --> 06:16.000
You must be Teresa.

06:16.000 --> 06:18.250
Yeah. Who are you?

06:18.250 --> 06:22.125
I'm Mickey Donovan.
I'm gonna be your new father.

06:22.125 --> 06:24.000
You're a beauty.

06:24.000 --> 06:25.875
Here.

06:30.291 --> 06:33.667
Bunchy won
the fucking lottery, huh?

06:33.667 --> 06:35.333
I like to call him Brendan.

06:35.333 --> 06:38.667
You can call him fucking
Vladimir, for all I care,

06:38.667 --> 06:39.959
as long as you
treat him right.

06:39.959 --> 06:41.834
But he's never loved.

06:41.834 --> 06:44.500
He's pure,
so you be gentle with my boy.

06:44.500 --> 06:47.875
[clears throat]
I see you two have met.

06:51.333 --> 06:52.834
You going out?

06:52.834 --> 06:55.041
Yeah.
Come on, Pop.

06:55.041 --> 06:57.250
He's helping me out with
a little project I got going.

06:57.250 --> 06:59.291
Brendan told me
all about your project.

06:59.291 --> 07:03.542
I'm telling you,
be gentle with my boy.

07:14.583 --> 07:17.667
[jazz music playing on radio]

07:17.667 --> 07:22.542
♪♪♪

07:28.959 --> 07:32.208
Already up and back to work--
good for you.

07:32.208 --> 07:34.208
Yeah, well,
I was up all night.

07:34.208 --> 07:35.583
Couldn't sleep.

07:35.583 --> 07:37.500
That hornet's nest
you opened up--

07:37.500 --> 07:38.917
Why didn't you tell me
you was gonna do that, man?

07:38.917 --> 07:41.208
Look on the bright side.
Maybe they learned a big lesson.

07:41.208 --> 07:43.166
Don't fuck
with the Donovans.

07:43.166 --> 07:44.583
- Hey, Mick.
- Hey, sweetie. Mwah.

07:47.083 --> 07:49.417
- Thanks, baby.
- Yeah.

07:49.417 --> 07:50.959
How about you, Pop?
Did you sleep?

07:50.959 --> 07:53.959
I'll sleep enough
when I'm dead.

07:53.959 --> 07:58.750
Guess who met the soon-to-be
Mrs. Brendan Donovan.

08:00.208 --> 08:02.709
Yeah, Pop
brought her flowers.

08:02.709 --> 08:06.458
Tulips--reminded me
of a lovely girl I once knew,

08:06.458 --> 08:09.041
a knockout stripper
from Amsterdam.

08:09.041 --> 08:10.291
Was a wonderful soul.

08:10.291 --> 08:11.917
First time I was with her,

08:11.917 --> 08:16.417
I felt something hard
in her breast--a lump.

08:16.417 --> 08:19.291
She died from it.

08:19.291 --> 08:22.125
So many good women gone.

08:25.458 --> 08:27.000
How'd I get on to this?

08:27.000 --> 08:28.792
You were talking about tulips
that you bought

08:28.792 --> 08:31.458
- for Bunchy's girl.
- Oh, right.

08:31.458 --> 08:33.834
Let's toast to Bunchy
and to love.

08:33.834 --> 08:37.000
[glass shatters]
- What the hell? What was that?

08:37.000 --> 08:38.083
Fuck. No.

08:38.083 --> 08:40.250
[tires squealing]

08:40.250 --> 08:42.959
Shit. Oh, fuck,
not my car.

08:42.959 --> 08:45.625
[vehicle departing rapidly]

08:47.500 --> 08:51.625
[car alarm blaring]

08:51.625 --> 08:53.667
[sighs]

08:53.667 --> 08:55.625
[dog barking in the distance]

08:58.500 --> 09:00.166
It's fucking fantastic.

09:00.166 --> 09:02.166
- What are you talking about?
- Oh, come on.

09:02.166 --> 09:04.834
This is the best plan
you came up with in years.

09:04.834 --> 09:07.458
- When does Napier land?
- An hour.

09:07.458 --> 09:09.166
[Helen]
I'm very worried about this.

09:09.166 --> 09:10.959
I hardly ever
have business on this side

09:10.959 --> 09:14.125
- of the building anymore.
- Well, you do today.

09:14.125 --> 09:15.917
Where are they?

09:15.917 --> 09:17.583
They're in the back.

09:22.709 --> 09:26.166
These are Central American
eyelash vipers.

09:26.166 --> 09:31.041
Uh, Customs confiscated them
48 hours ago at LAX.

09:31.041 --> 09:34.333
- What's in 'em?
- They're packed with condoms

09:34.333 --> 09:36.000
full of black tar heroin.

09:36.000 --> 09:39.458
Look, this is very dangerous
and completely illegal.

09:39.458 --> 09:41.667
Relax, Helen.
We'll dope the snakes.

09:41.667 --> 09:43.166
All you got to do
is show up at the airport

09:43.166 --> 09:44.250
with your warden badge.

09:47.375 --> 09:48.458
You ready?

09:52.667 --> 09:53.709
Here.

09:57.458 --> 09:58.542
You ready?

10:00.458 --> 10:03.542
[snakes hissing]

10:10.000 --> 10:11.500
[Muncie]
You want to tell me

10:11.500 --> 10:13.959
who microwaved the car?

10:13.959 --> 10:17.959
I have no idea--
maybe local kids.

10:17.959 --> 10:19.709
I know what you're up to,
Mr. Donovan--

10:19.709 --> 10:21.375
selling coke
and running girls.

10:21.375 --> 10:22.709
What are you talking about?

10:22.709 --> 10:26.917
Do you have any idea
who you're in with?

10:26.917 --> 10:30.458
I'd like to be in with you,
Detective.

10:30.458 --> 10:32.875
I'm gonna think about that
attractive offer all night long.

10:32.875 --> 10:35.000
I just love old white men.

10:35.000 --> 10:37.834
Oh, that hurts.

10:37.834 --> 10:39.458
Heard of APS--

10:39.458 --> 10:40.667
Armenian Power Syndicate?

10:40.667 --> 10:42.834
I wouldn't know an Armenian
from a Russian

10:42.834 --> 10:45.333
from a fucking
German Shepherd.

10:48.291 --> 10:50.417
I understand you have
a history

10:50.417 --> 10:52.125
of being helpful
to law enforcement.

10:55.583 --> 10:57.750
I'd like you
to start helping again.

11:02.166 --> 11:04.709
Working with us is the only
way you and your kids

11:04.709 --> 11:06.625
are coming out of this
with all your arms and legs

11:06.625 --> 11:08.709
still attached.

11:10.417 --> 11:12.125
I ain't done nothing wrong,

11:12.125 --> 11:14.917
and I ain't talking
to nobody about nothing.

11:14.917 --> 11:16.625
Okay.

11:16.625 --> 11:18.792
You are shut down
as of today.

11:18.792 --> 11:20.917
Vice guys are gonna watch
this building.

11:20.917 --> 11:23.750
We see any activity,
I'm bringing you and those two

11:23.750 --> 11:27.083
up on narcotics
and trafficking charges.

11:27.083 --> 11:30.834
You want to get
us feeling more cooperative...

11:30.834 --> 11:32.417
better give me a call.

11:32.417 --> 11:34.458
Do the right thing.

11:36.583 --> 11:39.792
[indistinct chatter
over police radio]

11:44.792 --> 11:47.125
All right, Pop, talk to me.
What are we doing?

11:47.125 --> 11:50.166
Package up what's left
of the coke and hide it.

11:50.166 --> 11:52.041
Call Ginger.

11:52.041 --> 11:53.625
No appointments today.

11:53.625 --> 11:57.500
Go home.
I'll call you tonight.

11:57.500 --> 11:59.333
You good?

11:59.333 --> 12:01.667
Yeah.

12:01.667 --> 12:03.709
[Helen]
Are we getting on a plane?

12:03.709 --> 12:06.291
Oh, we're gonna meet Lena--
put the snakes in his golf bag.

12:06.291 --> 12:07.667
In a golf bag?

12:07.667 --> 12:09.500
She'll get the luggage
in his car.

12:09.500 --> 12:11.250
All you got to do is grab
Napier, flash him your badge,

12:11.250 --> 12:13.125
and tell him he's under arrest
for smuggling.

12:13.125 --> 12:14.792
Charge him
with smuggling snakes...

12:14.792 --> 12:17.083
- Full of heroin.
- Full of heroin into the U.S.

12:17.083 --> 12:19.500
and then, um,
threaten to call the DEA.

12:19.500 --> 12:22.667
Helen, all you got to do
is present him with the charges,

12:22.667 --> 12:23.959
and I'll take over, okay?

12:23.959 --> 12:25.083
Okay.

12:25.083 --> 12:26.166
- You all right?
- Yeah.

12:26.166 --> 12:27.667
That's Napier's plane.

12:27.667 --> 12:29.500
- Let's do it.
- Wait. I'm sorry.

12:29.500 --> 12:30.834
I'm sorry.
I can't do this.

12:30.834 --> 12:32.542
I'll give you all the money
back--all of it.

12:32.542 --> 12:33.875
We could all get
in a lot of trouble.

12:33.875 --> 12:36.709
- Give me the--
- What the fuck are you doing?

12:36.709 --> 12:37.917
What? What do you
want from me, huh?

12:37.917 --> 12:39.959
- She hit me.
- I'm sorry, Helen.

12:39.959 --> 12:41.709
You were hysterical, okay?

12:41.709 --> 12:43.125
Oh, my God.
Aah!

12:43.125 --> 12:46.709
[vehicle approaching]

12:46.709 --> 12:49.875
[cell phone ringing]

12:54.250 --> 12:55.583
Yeah?

12:58.792 --> 13:00.875
Don't worry.

13:03.500 --> 13:05.625
I said don't worry.

13:08.000 --> 13:10.375
[shovel clatters]

13:13.166 --> 13:14.291
[Helen]
I can't breathe.

13:14.291 --> 13:16.250
I can't breathe.
Oh, my God.

13:16.250 --> 13:18.375
Oh.
Holy shit!

13:18.375 --> 13:20.917
Look at my leg.

13:20.917 --> 13:22.709
We're gonna get you
to a hospital.

13:22.709 --> 13:24.750
I can feel
my face swelling up.

13:24.750 --> 13:26.583
Your face isn't swelling up.
Put your feet in the car.

13:26.583 --> 13:28.333
Are my lips turning black?

13:28.333 --> 13:30.250
Get her out of here.

13:30.250 --> 13:33.083
[tires squealing]

13:40.750 --> 13:44.166
[cell phone dialing,
line trilling]

13:44.166 --> 13:46.083
This is Paige.
Leave a message.

13:46.083 --> 13:50.000
- [cell phone beeps]
- Paige, the Napier thing...

13:50.000 --> 13:52.583
it's not gonna happen.

13:52.583 --> 13:56.125
[cell phone beeps]

13:56.125 --> 13:59.208
Tulips are one of my all-time
favorite flowers.

13:59.208 --> 14:01.792
If you love tulips and you have
a favorite color, I'd love to--

14:01.792 --> 14:04.291
The Plein Air Collection
in the dining room...?

14:04.291 --> 14:06.166
Take it.

14:06.166 --> 14:07.500
Well, we bought them together,
so I just wanted to--

14:07.500 --> 14:09.458
Take them.

14:09.458 --> 14:11.709
Thank you.

14:11.709 --> 14:13.375
Varick, I know
you didn't come up here

14:13.375 --> 14:15.291
to discuss art, so...
what?

14:15.291 --> 14:17.375
[sighs]

14:17.375 --> 14:19.250
[chuckles]

14:19.250 --> 14:21.291
Your father's
getting rid of me.

14:21.291 --> 14:24.041
He's cutting me out
completely, Paige.

14:24.041 --> 14:25.792
Does that surprise you?

14:28.041 --> 14:29.959
May--maybe
just speak to him.

14:31.875 --> 14:33.959
Tell him to honor the promises
that he made me.

14:33.959 --> 14:35.500
You want me to speak
to my father on your behalf?

14:35.500 --> 14:38.333
I've helped run this company
for almost 20 years.

14:38.333 --> 14:41.000
I'm a member of this family.
The least you can do--

14:41.000 --> 14:44.375
No. See, you've worn
the clothes so fucking long,

14:44.375 --> 14:46.750
you forgot
they don't belong to you.

14:46.750 --> 14:48.917
What you should do
is say thank you

14:48.917 --> 14:51.041
and get out.

14:58.625 --> 15:01.166
What's the problem, Terry?

15:01.166 --> 15:03.667
Why won't you
move in with us?

15:03.667 --> 15:05.500
I'm fine where I am.

15:05.500 --> 15:08.333
[razor buzzing]

15:08.333 --> 15:09.542
Look...

15:09.542 --> 15:12.000
that's the one--
the Balbo.

15:13.583 --> 15:16.000
I'll just have
a clean shave.

15:17.750 --> 15:19.375
You're no fun.

15:19.375 --> 15:20.875
You're glum.

15:20.875 --> 15:23.041
All you guys
are so fucking glum.

15:25.917 --> 15:27.542
Here...

15:29.625 --> 15:31.917
You can read
the articles.

15:38.542 --> 15:41.959
It wouldn't kill you
to come look at the room.

15:41.959 --> 15:43.208
Tell me how fucking great
it looks.

15:43.208 --> 15:44.792
[man]
Ready, sir.

15:50.917 --> 15:53.542
[sighs]

15:57.625 --> 16:00.083
There will be an unexpected

16:00.083 --> 16:02.875
and totally unplanned
pop quiz tomorrow.

16:02.875 --> 16:05.917
You're welcome
for the heads-up.

16:05.917 --> 16:08.417
Please take advantage
and study.

16:12.750 --> 16:14.291
I, um...

16:14.291 --> 16:17.834
I could use some more help
with those proofs.

16:17.834 --> 16:20.583
Do you still want to get
that cup of coffee?

16:20.583 --> 16:21.875
Um...

16:21.875 --> 16:25.458
listen, I shouldn't have
texted you back.

16:25.458 --> 16:27.458
That was a mistake.

16:27.458 --> 16:29.875
So why did you?

16:29.875 --> 16:33.250
Because I was being
totally fucking inappropriate.

16:33.250 --> 16:35.000
Got it.

16:35.000 --> 16:36.792
I'm sorry.

16:36.792 --> 16:38.959
Listen,
I take pain medicine

16:38.959 --> 16:41.667
because of the accident.

16:41.667 --> 16:45.667
I wasn't myself
when I texted.

16:45.667 --> 16:48.542
I know you just want to talk,
but you're my student.

16:48.542 --> 16:51.709
We have to keep it
to school.

16:51.709 --> 16:53.500
I have a faculty meeting,
Bridget.

16:53.500 --> 16:55.750
Excuse me.

16:55.750 --> 16:59.125
[indistinct chatter]

17:18.208 --> 17:21.458
[door opens]

17:21.458 --> 17:23.917
[door closes]

17:38.000 --> 17:39.709
What the fuck
are you doing here?

17:39.709 --> 17:41.709
I'm sorry.

17:41.709 --> 17:43.291
I'm sorry I misled you,
Brendan.

17:43.291 --> 17:44.834
You fucking lied to me.

17:44.834 --> 17:47.000
I had an obligation.

17:47.000 --> 17:50.000
I needed to know
what happened to him.

